'''Conditional release''' is a method of release from [[incarceration]] that is contingent upon obeying conditions of release under threat of revocation (return to prison) under reduced [[due process]] protections."<ref>{{cite journal|author=Doherty, Fiona|title=Indeterminate Sentencing Returns: The Invention of Supervised Release|volume=88|journal=N.Y.U. L. Rev.|number=958|date=2013}}</ref> Hence, conditional release can be a synonym of [[parole]] and is sometimes viewed as a less restrictive alternative to hospitalizing psychiatric patients.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Conditional release: a less restrictive alternative to hospitalization?|journal=Psychiatric Services|volume=57|issue=11|pages=1600–6|pmid=17085608|year=2006|author1=Segal|first1=S. P.|last2=Burgess|first2=P. M.|doi=10.1176/appi.ps.57.11.1600}}</ref>

